\f0\b\fs20 \cf4 \super \strokec4 14\'a0
\f1\b0\fs24 \nosupersub At mealtime Boaz said to her, \'93Come over here. Have some bread\'a0and dip it in the wine vinegar.\'94\cf2 \strokec2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\qc\partightenfactor0
\cf4 \strokec4 When she sat down with the harvesters,\'a0he offered her some roasted grain.\'a0She ate all she wanted and had some left over.\'a0
\f0\b\fs20 \super 15\'a0
\f1\b0\fs24 \nosupersub As she got up to glean, Boaz gave orders to his men, \'93Let her gather among the sheaves\'a0and don\'92t reprimand her.\'a0
\f0\b\fs20 \super 16\'a0
\f1\b0\fs24 \nosupersub Even pull out some stalks for her from the bundles and leave them for her to pick up, and don\'92t rebuke\'a0her.\'94\cf2 \strokec2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\qc\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs20 \cf4 \super \strokec4 17\'a0
\f1\b0\fs24 \nosupersub So Ruth gleaned in the field until evening. Then she threshed\'a0the barley she had gathered, and it amounted to about an ephah.\'a0
\f0\b\fs20 \super 18\'a0
\f1\b0\fs24 \nosupersub She carried it back to town, and her mother-in-law saw how much she had gathered. Ruth also brought out and gave her what she had left over\'a0after she had eaten enough.\cf2 \strokec2 \

\f0\b\fs20 \cf4 \super \strokec4 19\'a0
\f1\b0\fs24 \nosupersub Her mother-in-law asked her, \'93Where did you glean today? Where did you work? Blessed be the man who took notice of you!\'94\cf2 \strokec2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\qc\partightenfactor0
\cf4 \strokec4 Then Ruth told her mother-in-law about the one at whose place she had been working. \'93The name of the man I worked with today is Boaz,\'94 she said.\cf2 \strokec2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\qc\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs20 \cf4 \super \strokec4 20\'a0
\f1\b0\fs24 \nosupersub \'93The\'a0Lord\'a0bless him!\'94 Naomi said to her daughter-in-law.\'a0\'93He has not stopped showing his kindness\'a0to the living and the dead.\'94 She added, \'93That man is our close relative;\'a0he is one of our guardian-redeemers.\'94\cf2 \strokec2 \

\f0\b\fs20 \cf4 \super \strokec4 21\'a0
\f1\b0\fs24 \nosupersub Then Ruth the Moabite\'a0said, \'93He even said to me, \'91Stay with my workers until they finish harvesting all my grain.\'92\'94\cf2 \strokec2 \

\f0\b\fs20 \cf4 \super \strokec4 22\'a0
\f1\b0\fs24 \nosupersub Naomi said to Ruth her daughter-in-law, \'93It will be good for you, my daughter, to go with the women who work for him, because in someone else\'92s field you might be harmed.\'94\cf2 \strokec2 \

\f0\b\fs20 \cf4 \super \strokec4 23\'a0
\f1\b0\fs24 \nosupersub So Ruth stayed close to the women of Boaz to glean until the barley\'a0and wheat harvests\'a0were finished. And she lived with her mother-in-law.\'a0 Ruth 2\cf2 \strokec2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
